# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
#  FINANCE INSIGHTS ENGINE — environment variables
#  Copy this file to .env and fill in your values.
#  Never commit .env to git.
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# ── SUPABASE ──────────────────────────────────────
# Found in: Supabase dashboard → Settings → API.

# Your project URL — safe to share, not a secret.
SUPABASE_URL=

# Anon (public) key — used by the backend as the baseline client.
# By itself it grants nothing; the caller's Clerk JWT is attached per
# request via postgrest.auth() so RLS evaluates against the end user.
# Safe to share with the frontend — it's a public key.
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# Service role key — KEEP THIS SECRET.
# NOT currently read by the backend (build_user_client uses the anon key
# above). Kept here only if you plan to add admin-tier operations that
# must bypass RLS. Never send this to the frontend.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY=

# ── AI PROVIDER ───────────────────────────────────
# LiteLLM reads provider keys by their standard env names.
# Only set the key for the provider you're using.

# Model string — this is the only line you change to switch providers:
#   anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001   → Anthropic  (default, fast + cheap)
#   anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6           → Anthropic  (smarter, costs more)
#   gpt-4o-mini                           → OpenAI
#   gemini/gemini-1.5-flash               → Google
#   groq/llama-3.1-8b-instant             → Groq (has free tier)
AI_MODEL=anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001

# Anthropic — get from console.anthropic.com.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Uncomment if switching to a different provider:
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# GEMINI_API_KEY=
# GROQ_API_KEY=

# ── APP ───────────────────────────────────────────

# development | production — controls debug mode and log verbosity.
APP_ENV=development

# Comma-separated list of allowed frontend origins for CORS.
# Add your Vercel URL here when you deploy the React app.
CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://localhost:5173

# ── AUTH (Clerk Third-Party Auth) ─────────────────
# Required. Copy from Clerk dashboard → JWT Templates → supabase → Issuer.
# The backend verifies RS256 JWTs against {CLERK_ISSUER}/.well-known/jwks.json
# and enforces iss/aud/exp/sub. Missing at boot ⇒ ValidationError (intentional).
# See docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-23-clerk-rs256-jwks-migration-design.md
# for the full auth model.
CLERK_ISSUER=
